            <h3 class="text">Welcome to the Intoxicated Cactuar</h3>

            <div class="text">

                <div class="center">

                    Are you fed up with snacks and drinks that don't pointlessly reference nerdy games, movies, books, and TV shows?

                    <br />
                    <br /> Do you routinely get thrown out of bars after angrily demanding to be served a drink that "tastes like
                    the Hypnotoad from
                    <strong>Futurama</strong>"?

                    <br />
                    <br /> Would you sooner punch yourself in the face than eat one more marshmallow-esque dessert that isn't shaped
                    like Kirby or Mallow?

                    <br />
                    <br /> Did you come
                    <i>this</i> close to divorcing your spouse the last time he/she poured you a martini that didn't reference
                    a Terry Prachett novel?

                    <br />
                    <br /> Did a woman recently break up with you - even though you weren't dating her - because you wouldn't shut
                    up about how good the food in
                    <strong>Final Fantasy XV</strong> looks?

                    <br />
                    <br /> Welcome home.

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>

        <br />

        <div class="post">

            <h3 class="text">Searching Our Recipes</h3>

            <div class="text">

                <div class="center">

                    Our site's beauty is its simplicity...because we couldn't be asked to make it beautifully complex.

                    <br />
                    <br /> At the
                    <a class="top" href="#top">Top of This Page</a> you'll find a
                    <strong>Search Bar</strong>. Above that, you'll find two
                    <strong>Dropdown Buttons</strong>.

                    <br />
                    <br /> Simply use the
                    <strong>Upper/Left Dropdown</strong> to tell us if you're searching for a
                    <strong>Food</strong> recipe or a
                    <strong>Drink</strong> recipe.

                    <br />
                    <br /> Next, use the
                    <strong>Upper/Right Dropdown</strong> to tell us if you're looking for the name of a
                    <strong>Recipe</strong> or the name of a recipe's
                    <strong>Source</strong> (the game, movie, book, or show the recipe came from).

                    <br />
                    <br /> Once you've done all that, just type something into the
                    <strong>Search Bar</strong>, click the
                    <strong>Search</strong> button, and voila!

                    <br />
                    <br /> Not quite sure what you're looking for yet? Well, just click one of the
                    <strong>All Drinks</strong> or
                    <strong>All Food</strong> buttons at the top of the page (or below) and start looking around!

                    <br />
                    <br />

                    <div class="button-jon">

